comments: Nesmith (BOS) legally contests Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of Mavericks possession stands.
Cauley-Stein (DAL) establishes himself in a legal position in Brown's (BOS) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact during the pick.
Brunson (DAL) seeks out the contact unnaturally with Walker (BOS) during his jump shot attempt. Walker maintains a legal guarding position with his arms vertical when the contact occurs.
Walker (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position on Brunson (DAL) during the drive.
Doncic (DAL) makes contact with the ball as he deflects the pass intended for Brown (BOS).
Brown (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position on Doncic (DAL) during the drive and the contact that occurs is incidental.
Tatum (BOS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with Brown's (BOS) off-arm during his driving shot attempt.
